                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d795">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Count <persName
                            type="to">Cassini</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-09-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The matter of the <hi rend="italic">Lena</hi> at San Francisco is having the
                    instant attention of this Department. Precise information is being sought as to
                    the condition of the boilers, machinery, and hull of the ship and the extent and
                    duration of the repairs needed to enable her to put to sea. It appears so far
                    that very extensive repairs are asked, amounting to virtual renovation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
